'''''Hornby Track Master''''' is a software tool to design [[Hornby Railways]] train tracks.

==Gameplay==
Hornby Track-Master is a birds eye 2D Planning tool. It is unlike [[Hornby Virtual Railway|Hornby Virtual Railway]]. [[Hornby Virtual Railway|HVR]]<ref>HVR And HVR2 Stands for "Hornby Virtual Railway 1" or the same but 2</ref> Uses a 3D Planning Enviroment in witch you plan, build and test you layout. How ever, being [[Hornby Virtual Railway|HVR]] Being released many years ago has bad Graphics. Also Hornby Track-Master developes a Shopping list for every thing needed to build it, but it has no 3D where as [[Hornby Virtual Railway|HVR]] Dose but dose Develope a shopping list.

Users select pieces of track from lists and places them where the user wishs. Track-Master use birds eye view to work. Track, Platforms, turntables etc can be added, once completed the software developes a printable shopping list<ref>A list of every part needed for layout the user planned and all the HORNBY prices</ref> which see people can go out and but the things they need with out buying to much and wasting it or buying to less and having to go back

==Hornby Track-Master (2011)==
'''[[Hornby Railways|Hornby]]''' is soon<ref>Hornby Trackmaster all read being late by a few months</ref> about to Release a new program. This program is called Track-Master, Track-Master is a 2D planning Enviroment. People select pieces of track from lists and places them where the user wishs. Track-Master use birds eye view to work. Track, Platforms, turntables etc can be added, once completed the software developes a printable shopping list which see people can go out and but the things they need with out buying to much and wasting it or buying to less and having to go back
